y over who the hosts are, although if I were going to do so, I'd be picking people I trusted to run good raids.<br><br>My personal desire is that only people who have been to the planes numerous times in the past and are confident of their ability to organize a complex raid volunteer to host these.<br><br>So, who wants to hold a raid?<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ujustallyssia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Just Allyssia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ichuu.com/anicat.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(12/27/01 8:54:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ichuu.com/amazonally.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Public Hate/Fear Hosts</span><hr size=1> Question, &quot;True Public Signup&quot; ... So you're saying anyone who wants to go can go? <br><br>What if only 10 warriors sign up but no enchanters or clerics? You cannot recruit for your 'public raid'? <br><br>What if the bulk of them are 46-50 and you wanna hit the 2nd floor? <br><br>What if there are individuals who sign up who has an obvious issue with the bulk of people... they still get to go? <br><br>If you guys held a summit and the rules were specified, then perhaps we can update the inny.com page where it shows the Summit Rules about the Public Raids, cuz since I wasn't there I'm unclear on what they are, as I'm sure many are.  Please in any case. Thank you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p><BR><APPLET archive="http://www.ichuu.com/DuriusWaterPic.jar" width="300" height="250" align="BOTTOM" code="